    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-10T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="484"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.516/182: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-10T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 10, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Department’s telegram No. 28.<note n="8" xml:id="d484fn8">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> In general American business with one
                    exception has not kept large foreign currency balances in Chile. An approximate
                    estimate of the value of these deposits is $800,000 United States currency of
                    which about $600,000 belongs to the Dupont subsidiary.</p>
                <pb facs="0543" n="439" xml:id="pg_439"/>
                <p>In my informal written communication to the <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi>
                    authorities yesterday I referred to a former note addressed to the Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs of the <persName corresp="#p_MJE1">Montero</persName> government
                    in which I incorporated the policy in your telegram No. 24, May 28, 2 p.m.<note
                        n="9" xml:id="d484fn9">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_511">p. 511</ref>.</note> I
                    said that this policy applies not only to oil property but to all American
                    property in Chile. I then called attention to the adverse effect which the
                    decree quoted in my telegram No. 70, June 9, 4 p.m., would have on deposits in
                    foreign currency by Americans and on the obligation of American banks arising
                    from their trusteeship to all foreign currency depositors.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
